<seg id=1> Henan Talks With Foreign Financial Institutions </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> XINHUA NEWS AGENCY WIRE Beijing, Dec. 16 (Yu Haisheng reporting): The Henan provincial government held economic cooperation talks here today with more than one hundred representatives from eighty-eight foreign financial institutions with offices in Beijing, hoping to promote mutual understanding between Henan and the international financial world and to develop new investment channels for the province. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> In his opening address, People's Bank of China executive vice-president Chen Yuan said that the Chinese government has decided to increase development in the country's midwest, along with using over sixty percent of payments from both foreign banks and the government for the benefit of the area. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The chief representative in Beijing for the General Bank of Belgium said that foreign financial institutions stationed in Beijing intend to make a contribution to the development of Henan and the midwestern area of the country. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> Henan executive vice-governor Li Chengyu gave a presentation concerning his province's natural resources and the state of economic development there. </seg>
<seg id=6> He said that Henan not only has the hardware needed for foreign investment, but also, in accordance with national policy, has an integrated preferential policy for encouraging investment from and trade technology cooperation with the outside world. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Various departments of the provincial government announced projects for economic and technological cooperation, and had talks with representatives about potential projects as well. </seg>
</p>
